Day 1 - December 22, 2024

8:00 AM: Arrive at Copenhagen Airport (CPH). Take the T4 train directly from the airport to the city center. The estimated cost is around 5.

9:00 AM: Check into the Tivoli Hotel. The estimated cost per night is around 100.

10:00 AM: Have breakfast at Grd in Torvehallerne Market. The estimated cost is around 10.

11:00 AM: Visit the Botanical Gardens. It's a 10-minute walk from the market.

12:30 PM: Head to Rosenborg Castle and the King's Garden. The estimated cost is around 15.

2:00 PM: Visit Kastellet and the Gefion Fountain. It's a 20-minute walk from the castle.

3:00 PM: Visit The Little Mermaid statue, designed by a British artist to commemorate Shakespeare's work Romeo and Juliet. Remember to book your tickets in advance. The estimated cost is around 10.

4:00 PM: Visit Amalienborg Palace and watch the Changing of the Guard at 3:00 AM. The estimated cost is around 10.

5:00 PM: Visit Frederik's Church. It's a 5-minute walk from the palace.

6:00 PM: Walk to Nyhavn. It's a 2-hour walk from Amalienborg Palace, so take your time and enjoy the city views.

7:00 PM: Have dinner at one of the restaurants in Nyhavn. The estimated cost is around 20.

Day 2 - December 23, 2024

8:00 AM: Start your day with a walk along Strget, Copenhagen's main shopping street.

10:00 AM: Have lunch at Kronborg Restaurant. The estimated cost is around 20.

11:30 AM: Visit the Round Tower. The estimated cost is around 5.

1:00 PM: Visit the Ny Carlsberg Glyptotek. The estimated cost is around 15.

3:00 PM: Visit the City Hall. It's a 10-minute walk from the Glyptotek.

4:00 PM: Spend the rest of your afternoon at Tivoli Gardens. Don't miss the chance to ride a polar bear, the most popular experience in the park. The estimated cost is around 20.

7:00 PM: Have dinner at a restaurant of your choice. The estimated cost is around 20.

9:00 PM: Take the T4 train to the airport. The estimated cost is around 5.

Please note that Copenhagen has mild temperatures in December around 30C, so pack light clothing. Also, remember to carry Euros cash for all your expenses. Enjoy your trip!

text:
Day 1: December 22, 2024

8:30 AM: Upon arrival at Copenhagen Airport, take a taxi to the city center. The fare should be around 20.

9:00 AM: Check-in at the Nordic Breeze hotel, located at Sankt Peders Strde 34, 1453 Copenhagen. This hotel costs 100 per night.

10:00 AM: Visit the National Museum of Denmark. The ticket costs 3 per person. Make sure to book your tickets in advance.

1:00 PM: Lunch at a local restaurant. Budget around 15-20 per person.

2:00 PM: Head to Amalienborg Palace. The Changing of the Guard ceremony is a must-see, which starts at 3:00 AM.

4:00 PM: Visit Rosenborg Castle. The entry fee is 8 per person.

6:00 PM: Head to Tivoli Gardens. At the park, you can ride a polar bear, which is the most popular experience in the park.

8:00 PM: Dinner at a restaurant in Tivoli Gardens. Budget around 20-25 per person.

Day 2: December 23, 2024

9:00 AM: Start your day at the Copenhagen Zoo. The entry fee is 10 per person.

12:00 PM: Lunch at a restaurant near the zoo. Budget around 15-20 per person.

1:00 PM: Visit SMK - The National Gallery of Denmark. The entry fee is 7 per person.

3:00 PM: Head to the Round Tower. The entry fee is 3 per person.

4:30 PM: Visit Christiansborg Palace. The entry fee is 10 per person.

6:45 PM: Take a taxi to the airport. The fare should be around 20.

In terms of clothing, Copenhagen has mild temperatures in December around 30C, so light clothing is recommended. For expenses, it's best to have Euros cash on hand as it's widely accepted in Copenhagen.
